      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Quick Presets + Safe Experiment Order",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "TI2V QUICK START\n\n1. Choose the first frame in the Load Image node.\n2. Describe the motion that begins from that exact frame.\n3. Tune FPS + seconds here; frame count is calculated automatically.\n4. Keep sequential_sage for the verified 16 GB baseline.\n5. First smoke test: 640×352, 20 FPS, 3 seconds, 24–30 steps. Raise to 40 steps after the chain is proven."
      ],
      "color": "#5b4615",
      "bgcolor": "#372b0e"
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        650,
        700
      ],
      "size": [
        570,
        300
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 12,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "How Progress Is Reported",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "PROGRESS\n\nStage 1 loads Dense 1.3B and the GPU-resident VAE.\nStage 2 sends the same center-cropped image through both Qwen rewrite stages and image-aware prompt encoding, then evicts Qwen.\nStage 3 encodes and fixes frame 0, then reports every denoise step, elapsed time, and ETA.\nStage 4 decodes.\nStage 5 optionally runs FlashVSR before RIFE and saves MP4."
      ],
      "color": "#243447",
      "bgcolor": "#182433"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        1260,
        700
      ],
      "size": [
        570,
        300
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "title": "Prompt Rules (Important)",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "PROMPTING\n\nDescribe motion and camera behavior, not details that contradict the source image. LingBot sees the actual first frame, so use phrases like “the supplied subject” and specify what changes over time. The Conditioned First Frame preview shows the exact center crop and resize that will be locked into latent frame 0."
      ],
      "color": "#4b2a2a",
      "bgcolor": "#301b1b"
    },
